President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals for judicial positions. Mark J. Bennett of Hawai ªi has been nominated to serve as a Circuit Judge on the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit. Andrew S. Oldham of Texas has been nominated to serve as a Circuit Judge on the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit. Michael Y. Scudder, Jr. of Illinois has been nominated to serve as a Circuit Judge on the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit. Amy J. St. Eve of Illinois has also been nominated to serve as a Circuit Judge on the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit. Nancy E. Brasel of Minnesota has been nominated to serve as a District Judge on the U.S. District Court for the District of Minnesota. Thomas S. Kleeh of West Virginia has been nominated to serve as a District Judge on the U.S. District Court for the Northern District of West Virginia. Peter J. Phipps of Pennsylvania has been nominated to serve as a District Judge on the U.S. District Court for the Western District of Pennsylvania. Eric C. Tostrud of Minnesota has been nominated to serve as a District Judge on the U.S. District Court for the District of Minnesota. C.J. Williams of Iowa has been nominated to serve as a District Judge on the U.S. District Court for the Northern District of Iowa.